The Parties agreed to step up bilateral and multi-bilateral development
cooperation, with an aim to support Myanmar development strategies and the
implementation of the Framework for Economic and Social Reforms, with a
particular emphasis on capacity-building. Cooperation shall take into account
jointly agreed priority sectors, such as rural development, the promotion of
micro-small and medium sized enterprises, the preservation of cultural heritage,
health, education, environmental protection, good governance.

Bilateral cooperation shall foster also cooperation between Local Governments,
Universities and NGOs.

Jointly agreed projects will be funded through grants, debt-swap and soft loans,
