Acknowledging the prominent role played by Prime Minister Monti to improve
the economic situation in Italy and in the Euro area, President U Thein Sein
expressed his confidence in the sustained efforts by Italy to strengthen the
reforms and improve the governance of the Euro area. He also noted that
Myanmar may become a promising hub for Italian business, thanks to its growth
prospects, domestic market potential and intra-regional trade which could prove
beneficial for Italy as well.

President U Thein Sein underlined Myanmar’s readiness to engage as a reliable
partner of the EU in Asia, namely within ASEAN whose chairmanship Myanmar
will hold in 2014, ASEM and other multilateral fora in the region.

Italy and Myanmar recognized the strategic value of ASEAN’s goal to become an
economic community in 2015. The emerging ASEAN community features very
interesting opportunities not only for ASEAN member States but also for Italy
and the European Union. Italy underlined Myanmar’s contribution to ASEAN’s
competitiveness through connectivity and deepened integration with the global
economy. Italy’s interest to exploit the opportunities offered by ASEAN
economic integration and to engage more with the region, as one of the most
dynamic for the global economy, was also stressed.

The two Parties underlined the ever growing relevance of ASEAN-EU relations,
as contacts and links at all levels become more frequent and significant. They
welcomed the prospect of negotiating a Myanmar-EU Investment Agreement and
expressed their commitment to work together towards a strengthened ASEAN-
EU partnership, in particular during their respective chairmanships of the two
organizations in 2014.

