Myanmar, marked a fundamental milestone in the relations between the two
countries.

The Parties exchanged views on the bilateral relations and on regional and
international issues of mutual interest. They agreed to further explore the vast
potential of bilateral partnership, particularly in the economic sector.

+++

Italy has followed with the utmost interest and deep appreciation the historic
changes in Myanmar over the last years at the initiative of President U Thein Sein
and his Government. In particular, Italy has always been supportive of the wide-
ranging reforms in the field of democratisation and rule of law as well as the
promotion and protection of human, social and labour rights. Italy is therefore
ready to actively support the sustained efforts for advancing those reforms under
President U Thein Sein’s guidance, the Government’s action and the Parliament’s
contribution. Italy has acknowledged that unprecedented remarkable progresses
have been achieved so far in the field of national reconciliation. In this regard it
encouraged Myanmar to continue to address the situation in Rakhine State also
through improving the status of local populations, the conflict in ethnic areas, in
particular with the Kachin, and the release of the remaining prisoners of
conscience. The Parties recognized the need to continue inclusive participation in
the political process.

The Parties underlined the importance of constructive engagement by Myanmar’s
regional partners, also within ASEAN, so as to contribute to long lasting
solutions to the political and economic challenges of the country.
