5. Milan Universal Exhibition 2015

The Parties welcome the Lebanese participation in Milan EXPO 2015 and are
convinced that Lebanon can pay a decisive contribution to the event. Sharing the view that
the EXPO 2015 key issue “Feeding the Planet, Energy for Life” is of fundamental
importance, they express particular appreciation for the cluster “Biomediterraneum” in
which Lebanon is taking part.

6. Institutional Twinnings and ENPI

The Parties reaffirm the importance of the opportunities for strengthening bilateral
cooperation offered by the EU program on institutional twinning.

They appreciate the participation of Italy, as a senior partner, in the implementation of
twinning projects in sectors such as the modernization of clearance procedures for the
Lebanese Customs.

They commit in promoting new joint initiatives which, in the framework of ENPI, may
help Lebanon to harmonize with European administrative standards and facilitate the
contacts between public institutions in the two Countries.

In the framework of European Neighbourhood and Partnership Instrument (ENPI) and
of the new European Partnership Instrument (ENI), the Parties agree to work closely to
ensure that fishery issues receive adequate attention and that the sector benefits from
sufficient support and funding.

They look favorably at the participation of Italian Institutions and Companies to the
bidding procedures launched by the European Commission/European Delegation in
Lebanon in the framework of EuropeAid programs, notably in the sectors of
infrastructures, agriculture and rural development, and environmental governance.

7. Resolution of commercial contr over sies

The Parties affirm the commitment to facilitate the solution of existing controversies
between Italian and Lebanese Companies, in order to enhance the respective business and
investment environment.
