PRESS RELEASE

The Council of Ministers, upon the proposal of the Minister of Economy and Finance, has approved
measures to increase the capital base of Banca Monte dei Paschi di Siena S.p.A. (MPS) thus
implementing the statement of EU Heads of State or Government of 26 October 2011 on measures
for restoring confidence in the banking sector. The Government has decided to act having regard to
the EBA Recommendation (EBA/REC/2011/1) of 8 December 2011 requiring to ensure that the
main European credit institutions increase their capital base by means of a temporary and
exceptional capital buffer in order to reach a 9% Core tier | ratio by 30 June 2012.

For MPS, the capital shortfall to reach the 9% level was initially quantified at about 3.3 billion
euros. The Bank of Italy has communicated that, taking into consideration the events occurred since
then (loss in the fourth quarter of 2011 and the evolution of the bank’s assets) and the actions
already taken by the bank and those in progress, the capital shortfall to reach the target of 9% Core
Tier 1, including the buffer for the sovereign risk, as estimated by MPS, would be in a range
between 1.3 and 1.7 billion euros.

The Government support to MPS is necessary to comply with the commitment made by Italy on the
occasion of the European Council of 26 October 2011, and having regard to the impossibility,
communicated by MPS to the Bank of Italy, to have recourse, for part of the recapitalization
requested by the EBA, to private solutions to strengthen the capital base, because of current highly
volatile market conditions.

The Government will subscribe new financial capitalization instruments comparable to special
bonds, similar to the so-called “Tremonti bond”. The Bank of Italy considered it appropriate, given
the uncertainties regarding the outcome of the actions still in progress, that the legislative
instrument provide for a maximum financial injection of 2 billion euros. The actual needed amount
will be determined by the bank close to the issuance.

With the new subscription, the “Tremonti bond”, issued by MPS in 2009 for an amount of 1.9
billion euros will be simultaneously redeemed. The maximum total amount of the new financial
instruments subscribed by the Government will therefore be 3.9 billion euros.

The subscription will be subject to a positive decision by the European Commission on the
compatibility of the scheme with the EU State aid regulatory framework and to the submission of a

restructuring plan by MPS.
