that each meeting of the ILJBC should be the occasion for a business delegation of each
Country to go to the other Country, in order to meet with local counterparts in ad hoc
encounters organized in advance (B2B meetings).

They encourage the ILJBC Board to define its strategic orientation and its annual work
plan for 2013 and the coming years and ensure their involvement in this activity through
the Italian Embassy in Beirut and the Lebanese Embassy in Rome which, according to the
Lebanese — Italian Business Council Agreement, are members of the Board with no voting
rights.

They welcome the decision of Promos to organize a business mission to Lebanon in
the first half of 2013.

2.Investments and Trade

The Parties acknowledge the excellent performance of bilateral trade reported in the
last years and highlight that a growth in the bilateral flows of goods and services is in the
mutual interest.

At the same time, bearing in mind that a more equilibrated and sustainable trade
balance brings mutual advantages, they express their commitment to the common objective
of expanding Lebanese exports to Italy. To this aim, they deem essential to achieve an
effective exchange of experience on respective export promotion practices.

The Parties underline the importance of the ongoing cooperation in the field of trade
fairs and recognize priority relevance to a mutual, qualified participation in the most
important Lebanese and Italian fairs and exhibitions.

The Parties recognize that the reciprocal incoming and outgoing flows of investments
have been lower than expected and do not match up the trade exchange volume, while at
the same time they are convinced that there is concrete scope to enhance them. For this
reason, they commit on the necessity of facilitating new investments in both Countries by
identifying appropriate means.

Each Party encourages the participation of its national companies in the bidding
procedures launched by the other Party.
